{{Quote|I am now able to reveal the existence of a secret unit in New Republic Intelligence called 'Alpha Red.' It is headed by Joi Eicroth, a xenobiologist formerly belonging to Alpha Blue, another secret unit charged with Yuuzhan Vong affairs. Since the beginning of the war, Alpha Red has undertaken covert research on Yuuzhan Vong biology with the assistance of a team of scientists supplied by the Chiss.|Director Dif Scaur|<ref name="Destiny" />}}
'''Alpha Red''' was a clandestine experimental research unit primarily within the [[New Republic Intelligence Service]] but also later within its successor agency, the [[Galactic Alliance Intelligence Service]]. Formed from members of the Intelligence Service's other secret unit, [[Alpha Blue]], along with several [[Chiss/Legends|Chiss]] [[Scientist/Legends|scientists]], Alpha Red was tasked with researching the [[Extragalactic/Legends|extra-galactic]] biology of the [[Yuuzhan Vong]]. They were to determine weaknesses in the Vong's biological systems and develop methods to exploit those weaknesses. The team was led by former Alpha Blue scientist [[Joi Eicroth]] and its staff included a group of [[Chiss/Legends|Chiss]] biotechnicians who worked alongside Intelligence scientists. They were able to create a dangerous toxin, also named [[Alpha Red (pathogen)|Alpha Red]].

==History==
{{Quote|Genocide is what the Emperor did. It's what the Yuuzhan Vong do. It shouldn't be what we do. If it is, I'm fighting for the wrong cause.|[[Wedge Antilles/Legends|Wedge Antilles]]|<ref name="Final Prophecy">''[[The New Jedi Order: The Final Prophecy]]''</ref>}}
Alpha Red was formed by [[Director of New Republic Intelligence]] [[Dif Scaur]] in the aftermath of the [[Battle of Coruscant (Yuuzhan Vong War)|capture]] of [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] by the [[Yuuzhan Vong]] from the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]]. Scaur had scientists from [[Alpha Blue]], a secret [[New Republic Intelligence Service]] unit, join with [[Chiss/Legends|Chiss]] [[Scientist/Legends|scientists]] to create the new secret unit. They were to study the Yuuzhan Vong and find a weakness that could be used in their biology to exploit.<ref name="CSWE">{{CSWECite|I|25|Alpha Red}}</ref>

The crowning achievement of Alpha Red's research was a biological weapon codenamed "[[Alpha Red (pathogen)|Alpha Red]]." The airborne pathogen proved in their laboratory tests to target a unique genetic strand amongst all Vong-related creatures, and destroy it. Alpha Red was also tested on sedated [[Warrior caste|Yuuzhan Vong warriors]]; the tests were successful in [[Death/Legends|killing]] them. Research was then moved out of the [[Chiss/Legends|Chiss]] research facility and into a converted hospital [[EF76 Nebulon-B escort frigate/Legends|EF76 Nebulon-B escort frigate]] located in orbit of [[Mon Calamari/Legends|Mon Calamari]] in order to produce tons of Alpha Red to distribute and unleash upon Yuuzhan Vong-held worlds. Upon hearing of the existence of the deadly Alpha Red pathogen by eavesdropping on a conversation between [[Mara Jade Skywalker|Mara Jade]] and [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]], [[Vergere]] infiltrated the facility and sabotaged the project.<ref name="Destiny" />

After the use of the pathogen was restricted to a last resort option and [[Vergere]]'s sabotage, Alpha Red was presumably shutdown. However, it was rediscovered by a strike team of [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] sent to destroy a [[yammosk]] on [[Caluula/Legends|Caluula]]. All the Yuuzhan Vong and their living technology were on the verge of death and very weak. A member of the strike team revealed that Alpha Red had been deployed on the planet. Upon discovering the reemergence of Alpha Red, Luke ordered all Yuuzhan Vong vessels in the system be destroyed to keep the bio-weapon at bay. [[Supreme Overlord]] [[Shimrra Jamaane]] sent an infected vessel to crash-land on [[Zonama Sekot/Legends|Zonama Sekot]] in order to destroy the planet, but his attack failed.<ref name="TUF" />

By [[138 ABY]], the [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lady]] [[Darth Maladi]], a member of the [[One Sith]], had found notes on Alpha Red and improved the weapon into a much deadlier version: [[Omega Red]].<ref name="leg2">[[Legacy — War 2|''Legacy — War'' 2]]</ref>

